#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.71:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:0.2"
msgid "7. Arahantavagga "
msgstr "7. The Perfected Ones "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.71:0.3"
msgid "71. Rādhasutta "
msgstr "71. With Rādha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.80, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā rādho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Rādha went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn22.71:1.3"
msgid "“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato, kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how does one know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ kiñci, rādha, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "“Rādha, one truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.5"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā … "
msgstr "One truly sees any kind of feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.71:1.6"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.71:1.7"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.71:1.8"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ … pe … yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya passati. "
msgstr "consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, rādha, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti … pe … "
msgstr "That’s how to know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.10"
msgid "aññataro ca panāyasmā rādho arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Rādha became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.71:1.11"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

